* To make something or someone seem more impressive or noteworthy than it really is;

**Normalizes** (verb)

* To bring something or someone back to a usual or ordinary state or condition;
* To make something or someone seem usual or ordinary again;
* To make something or someone seem unremarkable or unexceptional again;
* To make something or someone seem unimportant or unnoteworthy again;
* To make something or someone seem unremarkable or unexceptional again;

In other words, "glorifies" and "normalizes" are antonyms of each other, which means that they have opposite meanings. "Glorifies" means to make something or someone seem more important or wonderful, while "normalizes" means to make something or someone seem usual or ordinary.
